Document: EditorFileSystem
Path: godot/classes/class_editorfilesystem.rst
Summary: Provides methods for interacting with and managing Godot's filesystem within the editor, including scanning, reimporting, and querying file information.

Method: get_file_type(path: String) → String
Returns the resource type of the file, given the full path. This returns a string such as "Resource" or "GDScript", not a file extension such as ".gd".

Method: get_filesystem() → EditorFileSystemDirectory
Gets the root directory object.

Method: get_filesystem_path(path: String) → EditorFileSystemDirectory
Returns a view into the filesystem at path.

Method: get_scanning_progress() → float
Returns the scan progress for 0 to 1 if the FS is being scanned.

Method: is_importing() → bool
Returns true if resources are currently being imported.

Method: is_scanning() → bool
Returns true if the filesystem is being scanned.

Method: reimport_files(files: PackedStringArray)
Reimports a set of files. Call this if these files or their .import files were directly edited by script or an external program. If the file type changed or the file was newly created, use update_file or scan methods.
Note: This function blocks until the import is finished. However, the main loop iteration, including timers and Node._process, will occur during the import process due to progress bar updates. Avoid calls to reimport_files or scan while an import is in progress.

Method: scan()
Scan the filesystem for changes.

Method: scan_sources()
Check if the source of any imported resource changed.

Method: update_file(path: String)
Add a file in an existing directory, or schedule file information to be updated on editor restart. Can be used to update text files saved by an external program. This will not import the file. To reimport, call reimport_files or scan methods.